nsidering app deployment options**\\n\\nI’m working on verifying a process and considering using commands like osascript or ps for that. Maybe using `lsappinfo` could help identify app visibility. The user asked about deploying an app locally, which might need persistence, so I’m thinking it could be beneficial to create a simple app bundle inside the workspace. Since the repository has an install script, I might run that now. Ultimately, it seems safe to proceed with the installation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Executing installation script**\\n\\nI’m looking at our current manual process for building Molty, and it seems it’s still running, which might lead to duplicates. I should stop that process before running the install script. I want to log everything in the workspace, and it makes sense to execute `bash install-molty.sh` to capture the output. The script uses /tmp for compile errors only if it fails, so I can run it and gather the output. This should be a quick task to complete!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"手动运行验证已经通过，我继续把它安装到 `~/.openclaw/pets/Molty.app` 并注册为 LaunchAgent，这样才算“本地部署完成”。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7daf90c18819b8b7293a58a57e43a\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f3fXuFqcX6tOKHuXm8u7NDwC|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7dafa7fc0819ba8ea0594cb98b898","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd openclaw_projects/openclaw-pet-shufanli && if [ -f ../../checklists/_tmp/molty_run_20260328.pid ]; then kill $(cat ../../checklists/_tmp/molty_run_20260328.pid) 2>/dev/null || true; fi && bash install-molty.sh | tee ../../checklists/_tmp/install_molty_20260328.log && echo '---APP---' && ls -la ~/.openclaw/pets/Molty.app/Contents/MacOS && echo '---LAUNCHAGENT---' && ls -la ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ai.openclaw.molty.plist && echo '---PROC---' && pgrep -af '/Molty.app/Contents/MacOS/molty|ai.openclaw.molty|/pets/Molty.app' || true","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":180,"yieldMs"