{"type":"message","id":"cd6f5ac4","parentId":"af3fefb5","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:07:08.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring GitHub deployment options**\n\nI'm considering how to fetch the README and contents efficiently. Using the GitHub API could speed things up instead of waiting for a full clone, but for deployment, we do need to clone the repository. Maybe I could try `git clone --filter=blob:none`, but I'm already running the process. I could retry with a lighter approach. I also wonder if downloading the GitHub archive zip might be faster, although it could include large files. I might use sparse-checkout for efficiency as well. Let's check if I really need the entire release.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e0840360819b817a0b019a58a66e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpx-CJ3x0fxvPsK9GPfVipLmcuI_SWlcbFojO2yci53oW7S-mDzj_PSG3hJhXNXlwFu1wLhY031qkZ1x-2SOJTZGySNHIB-qS9pabaFu-BogGa0fCwlOt-YeImDi94bUFEWmaWgiLKF_9GNPJbTbRY8-9GAT2rJqx-ZkcyXBUxcLsz1f3tUsakPdLIHlKwubg-qoFkhxkkt8GXn0mjsN3gHrSI0p3FNqID-sOJzn0ZlvJEOlIf9qGI7zmf3foXyXEdEZUBdxDLTTIDTHJ298YqJad5CISkssazVgpIdj-kSZLxh7eAs0J1VU3Dc8pr0soZUD8XI4CPDsd68kkP_41ubEsCzHeTOlh13MwsLBmd0rWltrBrLvhtbx9pITVi_ZeoEFsW5lrDO4CZZgkY2qLlpHhq3aiVkSnsjBwZcsyymZOjLEC2ozyQtnJhcjAi_Je-QU-N4wVYKTCW5DvXjC6_u0mDFjL9i1kRPUCFCI-OFidg3ufIwPQDRlbuOl1MDQ97mEGNGDXObTdEZRdu-4hyV9AoHmRmkZDNqYaeysqPvZnjM0MeFxyQlXP61gaXKV-uY9rkoYU3MAg3VXWhkpl5KBOnJ8qgvT3D7dVJkYHHsIVkICKc5LF86LhQgM1fMGNceTz64hb5B3OQNIqyH054tOk5qIP5mavi0XasvUDzbQV_1NXPvBpzA745iOaebydUylCLXQTJVkffmiuODUWSLQUyC7ROHmBXYS0FMuwA5RKrJue4_Oll4uBBNQJkwx3V1qRmN6EsmX5RBdRJewFyE3qoNEOaFUnm-8DYqwv4GyUURDJd9Q0O5DUyfp4iBsY1FKte05nTb7Fu2DyUvo66GxqPqG3Nc1A04ZgHHdD665XkhbibNEZ33gqY69FkRu1vU4s0qtPSthHfoG5uwXrE3mjE7ay0z77VquXu0uO7Tx4x-BmJ4ZepcRTFezMFmA3015O5Bq_SVrKmEdtpVqTmypRNtyAVelAb3u9WDmkKD_53wUeS_cEHNhoCqE_X7Qp_DlcNVjdFtKp-XtXZ0Jq5qPIq9qGpSn-DYofvPbhglaY_nL5sCdDReNTHBjOtqrEfjfe3QHHalQmbRavJW6d6Dr