{"type":"message","id":"1e335592","parentId":"5f3d940e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:13:11.721Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring development options**\n\nI'm thinking about whether to compare architecture without fully localizing the giant assets and network requirements. It might be better to fetch only the minimal files needed to start development, maybe even in headless mode. I could also look into using the contents API to reconstruct the repo minus those large assets. However, I would need to verify local startup and build validation. Running commands like `npm install` could help determine if everything works without requiring all the assets. I'll need to validate my installation approach too.\n\n**Considering API options for downloads**\n\nI'm exploring the idea of using the GitHub API to download raw files from a repository in parallel, since there are only 98 files. I could possibly script this using the tree API along with raw.githubusercontent URLs, which might be faster than cloning the whole repo due to smaller requests. Most of the files are blobs, averaging around 20MB. I could curl 4 to 8 files at a time. I think I'll try using a Python script to list the files and construct the raw URLs effectively.","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e1e02cc8819bb028ad8e22849caa\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpx-Hu41rtjDP22COC6AOeyKZ5tWlLIAWCbUZ_JJ56AUQS-hQsY0MhPCL0gq5vc6sAm-n_2VWHS1w7GvxAAKj0IbtYFJLHYSeORbideB6He9OgtPlXusy8JNYxSuoJ0YuV9IMOfwpxAwfOKRl3OMq-AYVNQSgZJpSduU-P3QuU6ZcCuB6rzhlORK6pZmN5uOi9v5XZLKDb-vM_kkbw1Is364cgUCVwXsDotcC9P9iM3nyopGP0MePJe8KsdiO46OA7LouKGSlnF_7Nt_amVcyzDaZ1tCU_gCs-W0jO7fQoGMiJRqSUFoZqcDnTaPTVB2TZTfmo09GCN8YaNwNTu-bjPoiJm997-WG7FxjH2OrUtxTEPo7Do6SyFPqTeU2jYGNRfAceXg5UCTMO04o6rbM83cJuZ5tLuqZm7e1LXMRmXg6ftX_FcsnfnPlsUuYimreVnOXW_UqX_hNpDi8Gs0yJ-uvDIa0S3OLXnhceYfN8gbBod3FN7GAEq9eNY5mMVLkHeXvPYfx528gki5VIF8wV7MHssboQ6-tQ68_1DYZ7ZaUwPS6qpqYH1i5hP5u