g commands like `npm install` could help determine if everything works without requiring all the assets. I'll need to validate my installation approach too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering API options for downloads**\\n\\nI'm exploring the idea of using the GitHub API to download raw files from a repository in parallel, since there are only 98 files. I could possibly script this using the tree API along with raw.githubusercontent URLs, which might be faster than cloning the whole repo due to smaller requests. Most of the files are blobs, averaging around 20MB. I could curl 4 to 8 files at a time. I think I'll try using a Python script to list the files and construct the raw URLs effectively.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我换成“逐文件拉取”了：这个仓库只有 98 个文件，但有十几个 20MB 左右的大图，clone/codeload 在这台机子上不稳定；逐文件下载更可控。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e1eeef50819b86a35ff211860494\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5lHgaOMN36T8dUHHqGUa3f36|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e1f74208819ba7e50ba49510ceda","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"kill","sessionId":"brisk-forest"},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"kill\",\"sessionId\":\"brisk-forest\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_y1CpMohuhuy6XJ9y7nZisbtv|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e1f74230819baf39eb7dabccba9e","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"checklists/_tmp/download_blackbear_repo.py","content":"import json, os, subprocess, sys, urllib.request, pathlib, concurrent.futures\nfrom urllib.error import URLError, HTTPError\n\nWORKDIR = pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\nDEST = WORKDIR / 'openclaw_projects' / 'openclaw-pet-blackbear'\nOWNER = 'BlackBearCC'\nREPO = 'openclaw-pet'\nBRANCH = 'main'\nAPI = f\"repos/{OWNER}/{REPO}/git/trees/{BRANCH}?recursive=1\"\n\nDEST.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\nproc = subprocess.run(['gh', 'api', API], cwd=str(WORKDIR), capture_output=True, text=True)\nif proc.returncode != 0:\n    print(proc.stderr)\n    sys.exit(proc.returncode)\n\ndata = json.loads(proc.stdout)\nfiles = [t for t in data['tree'] if t.get('type') == 'blob']\n\n# Skip git metadata; fetch raw file contents\n\ndef fetch(item):\n    path = item['path']\n    url = f'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{OWNER}/{REPO}/{BRANCH}/{path}'\n    out = DEST / path\n    out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=120) as r:\n            content = r.read()\n        out.write_bytes(content)\n        return ('ok', path, len(content))\n    except (URLError, HTTPError, TimeoutError, Exception) as e:\n        return ('err', path, str(e))\n\noks = []\nerrs = []\nwith concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=6) as ex:\n    for res in ex.map(fetch, files):\n        if res[0] == 'ok':\n            oks.append(res)\n            print(f\"OK\\t{res[1]}\\t{res[2]}\")\n        else:\n            errs.append(res)\n            print(f\"ERR\\t{res[1]}\\t{res[2]}\", file=sys.stderr)\n\nprint(f'SUMMARY ok={len(oks)} err={len(errs)}')\nif errs:\n    sys.exit(2)\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"checklists/_tmp/download_blackbear_repo.py\",\"content\":\"import json, os, subprocess, sys, urllib.request, pathlib, concurrent.futures\\nfrom urllib.error import URLError, HTTPError\\n\\nWORKDIR = pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\\nDEST = WORKDIR / 'openclaw_projects' / 'openclaw-pet-blackbear'\\nOWNER = 'BlackBearCC'\\nREPO = 'openclaw-pet'\\nBRANCH = 'main'\\nAPI = f\\\"repos/{OWNER}/{REPO}/git/trees/{BRANCH}?recursive=1\\\"\\n\\nDEST.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\nproc = subprocess.run(['gh', 'api', API], cwd=str(WORKDIR), capture_output=True, text=True)\\nif proc.returncode != 0:\\n    print(proc.stderr)\\n    sys.exit(proc.returncode)\\n\\ndata = json.loads(proc.stdout)\\nfiles = [t for t in data['tree'] if t.get('type') == 'blob']\\n\\n# Skip git metadata; fetch raw file contents\\n\\ndef fetch(item):\\n    path = item['path']\\n    url = f'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{OWNER}/{REPO}/{BRANCH}/{path}'\\n    out = DEST / path\\n    out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n    try:\\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=120) as r:\\n            content = r.read()\\n        out.write_bytes(content)\\n        return ('ok', path, len(content))\\n    except (URLError, HTTPError, TimeoutError, Exception) as e:\\n        return ('err', path, str(e))\\n\\noks = []\\nerrs = []\\nwith concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=6) as ex:\\n    for res in ex.map(fetch, files):\\n        if res[0] == 'ok':\\n            oks.append(res)\\n            print(f\\\"OK\\\\t{res[1]}\\\\t{res[2]}\\\")\\n        else:\\n            errs.append(res)\\n            print(f\\\"ERR\\\\t{res[1]}\\\\t{res[2]}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\\nprint(f'SUMMARY ok={len(oks)} err={len(errs)}')\\nif errs:\\n    sys.exit(2)\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_sECe9gHZisXe60ba2EHSFUOE|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e1f74244819b9ea2624305a2b452","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py advance --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md --status active --updated '2026-03-28 22:12' --current '逐文件下载 BlackBearCC/openclaw-pet 并准备本地安装验证' --append-evidence '已切换为 GitHub tree+raw 逐文件下载方案，绕开大仓库 clone/codeload 卡顿' --clear-blockers","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":20,"yieldMs":1000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py advance --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md --status active --updated '2026-03-28 22:12' --current '逐文件下载 BlackBearCC/openclaw-pet 并准备本地安装验证' --append-evidence '已切换为 GitHub tree+raw 逐文件下载方案，绕开大仓库 clone/codeload 卡顿' --clear-blockers\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":20,\"yieldMs\":1000}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":234,"output":1273,"cacheRead":72576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74083,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":17747071