{"type":"message","id":"6308c9f8","parentId":"108ebb65","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:19:21.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering download strategy**\n\nI need to figure out if I should kill the current process and use a sequential method for the missing files. It seems like I'm still waiting on timeouts. If I do that, I could implement a retry or resume function instead. Counting the files, I have 43 total at 139MB, and 98 are good, so that's promising! I think a retry downloader could skip existing ones and fetch the missing ones, possibly using a maximum of 2 workers. Leveraging the tree API might be a good move here. Let’s proceed!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e35795e8819ba5291cf94a332031\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpx-Nb1yQNh6Le5DdNm465FtUVHlE6BiU0KuN2rdt3naX7LnOX-uC9i01SsWeoyLGQe7Z7D-m5QjPAjwRzWZ95m0yeAJYuON6f_JNAzASfqLIo-U9acM_yQiNiXl0b8vPDje3uq-PzhvdMs1pMQfp3LChUSvQH9WbutML9KDSfKM-gHNvLyGKAREsEhG1QHI60qF42dQcpOnDlmoNmHOE_VmvEiEQ32khlijfoacB_RcvHPekjD_S0feHXFrCg2Al5NzvvKYc-_RPNaQ32MyzZ2g0xkPn448nxQ6JYNSFL0JW6LuB8x6M1Yib3jY7RoBoQu4FG4OSh9EMnL25NVAHhrl68Uzj8i07zDVgeFkUEPwuKyib4XhfjMzMJZE4Ifk5g_Y_CVQOgnhcrqWi5ZOlc2t50qXyViOk2WvmA5ASC2oN5lZZ4dknOmUaNuCh0ba0CeINiyaCdzJlI1ldpuSDvGcyWQJCVvXijOoiBo-kGlWCah4AaC9onc5KikJdOlmkw71OxgeNqU8-KwoNfKBwjvhmnC85PSDsha2N_JJtTqIBD83FpKPuSy5jTYbW7YghR8BF9KNL_MDnngbY_loFSyMAIKTp8RWa91E5qHke6zfv2WZvantAPpSCy6l7pRes35GX6mX7wFHlUyCo5a8xn-G8ibwTsmfnfsj4Bko3tXLTv0FGD1QG3oIBSs3uJLD4zwths5tIqzuOzlBwHcpMtWx6MaNbWz6q1Vh4JGe9esE2IAA5EcJ7oOiHwppz6OWY52Z-tkCUWn75d3P1F0xftQvIAEPSklp0_GFXHSIQWNB-ywbEgendpdK_VlpdpytMipenw2z5511WeHAmWhKM6IcqMO_9vWeUBOwSHCTm_4D1TQ6nopa49ezevU8ruXqejviNxBUE9tZIL8lCtx4vgOXv2ZrVXjSCw53zkW6j_KZ1YglZU1Hys5Cp0UJ7xEtpn5_fss2Oq4EBNhdnX9zauWPJGRolqHtRDgWzVSvWWp0cdtf17TDImnDBDi6VJNbZ4SfYotOv5o4J3Z375tt5KD-f4ljjUdjlY5kverlGJ5e046nHsNm7CsfwHVsoQ3HCO4AYPRVh8xVxkEYZcVen541hX-x2zpI8Naasl6-0tiv_kbHZX8YdrG9rxV6Y19I6mFSAZPpNj1EsjG6HWrpW6299xlCh8HHEy_VMEJ9nuIrHuSWttborgxSKzGqo-RDqgp3vNfEXS2JRj05enRBLJkBLUWUR9OiV7b4_IyoWSz34dUzJrHK4pnuXNzedcFbRVfFUNyyZrn7TNKKjQZpyL5e2R3Q==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering download strategy**\\n\\nI need to figure out if I should kill the current process and use a sequential method for the missing files. It seems like I'm still waiting on timeouts. If I do that, I could implement a retry or resume function instead. Counting the files, I have 43 total at 139MB, and 98 are good, so that's promising! I think a retry downloader could skip existing ones and fetch the missing ones, possibly using a maximum of 2 workers. Leveraging the tree API might be a good move here. Let’s proceed!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"已经下载到 139MB / 43 个文件了，思路没问题；问题只是 raw 通道并发太高。我把它切成“断点续传 + 低并发重试”。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e35bae10819b92379999305a9055\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qVHN5c4gveV1x0HtXroii2d4|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e3688fb0819b9983242b65b296df","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"kill","sessionId":"neat-haven"},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"kill\",\"sessionId\":\"neat-haven\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8X4j2bxBph4bqNFCOB8IBu3W|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e3688fc0819bbab69cbb08ce4840","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"checklists/_tmp/download_blackbear_repo_resume.py","content":"import json, os, subprocess, sys, urllib.request, pathlib, concurrent.futures, time\nfrom urllib.error import URLError, HTTPError\n\nWORKDIR = pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\nDEST = WORKDIR / 'openclaw_projects' / 'openclaw-pet-blackbear'\nOWNER = 'BlackBearCC'\nREPO = 'openclaw-pet'\nBRANCH = 'main'\nAPI = f\"repos/{OWNER}/{REPO}/git/trees/{BRANCH}?recursive=1\"\n\nDEST.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\nproc = subprocess.run(['gh', 'api', API], cwd=str(WORKDIR), capture_output=True, text=True)\nif proc.returncode != 0:\n    print(proc.stderr)\n    sys.exit(proc.returncode)\n\ndata = json.loads(proc.stdout)\nfiles = [t for t in data['tree'] if t.get('type') == 'blob']\nmissing = []\nfor item in files:\n    p = DEST / item['path']\n    size = item.get('size')\n    if not p.exists() or (size is not None and p.stat().st_size != size):\n        missing.append(item)\n\nprint(f'MISSING {len(missing)} / TOTAL {len(files)}')\n\ndef fetch(item):\n    path = item['path']\n    url = f'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{OWNER}/{REPO}/{BRANCH}/{path}'\n    out = DEST / path\n    out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    last = None\n    for attempt in range(1, 6):\n        try:\n            with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=180) as r:\n                content = r.read()\n            out.write_bytes(content)\n            return ('ok', path, len(content), attempt)\n        except Exception as e:\n            last = e\n            time.sleep(min(20, attempt * 3))\n    return ('err', path, str(last), 5)\n\noks = []\nerrs = []\nwith concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=2) as ex:\n    for res in ex.map(fetch, missing):\n        if res[0] == 'ok':\n            oks.append(res)\n            print(f\"OK\\t{res[1]}\\t{res[2]}\\tattempt={res[3]}\")\n        else:\n            errs.append(res)\n            print(f\"ERR\\t{res[1]}\\t{res[2]}\\tattempt={res[3]}\", file=sys.stderr)\n\nprint(f'SUMMARY ok={len(oks)} err={len(errs)} remaining={len(errs)}')\nif errs:\n    sys.exit(2)\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"checklists/_tmp/download_blackbear_repo_resume.py\",\"content\":\"import json, os, subprocess, sys, urllib.request, pathlib, concurrent.futures, time\\nfrom urllib.error import URLError, HTTPError\\n\\nWORKDIR = pathlib.Path('/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace')\\nDEST = WORKDIR / 'openclaw_projects' / 'openclaw-pet-blackbear'\\nOWNER = 'BlackBearCC'\\nREPO = 'openclaw-pet'\\nBRANCH = 'main'\\nAPI = f\\\"repos/{OWNER}/{REPO}/git/trees/{BRANCH}?recursive=1\\\"\\n\\nDEST.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\nproc = subprocess.run(['gh', 'api', API], cwd=str(WORKDIR), capture_output=True, text=True)\\nif proc.returncode != 0:\\n    print(proc.stderr)\\n    sys.exit(proc.returncode)\\n\\ndata = json.loads(proc.stdout)\\nfiles = [t for t in data['tree'] if t.get('type') == 'blob']\\nmissing = []\\nfor item in files:\\n    p = DEST / item['path']\\n    size = item.get('size')\\n    if not p.exists() or (size is not None and p.stat().st_size != size):\\n        missing.append(item)\\n\\nprint(f'MISSING {len(missing)} / TOTAL {len(files)}')\\n\\ndef fetch(item):\\n    path = item['path']\\n    url = f'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/{OWNER}/{REPO}/{BRANCH}/{path}'\\n    out = DEST / path\\n    out.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n    last = None\\n    for attempt in range(1, 6):\\n        try:\\n            with urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=180) as r:\\n                content = r.read()\\n            out.write_bytes(content)\\n            return ('ok', path, len(content), attempt)\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            last = e\\n            time.sleep(min(20, attempt * 3))\\n    return ('err', path, str(last), 5)\\n\\noks = []\\nerrs = []\\nwith concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=2) as ex:\\n    for res in ex.map(fetch, missing):\\n        if res[0] == 'ok':\\n            oks.append(res)\\n            print(f\\\"OK\\\\t{res[1]}\\\\t{res[2]}\\\\tattempt={res[3]}\\\")\\n        else:\\n            errs.append(res)\\n            print(f\\\"ERR\\\\t{res[1]}\\\\t{res[2]}\\\\tattempt={res[3]}\\\", file=sys.stderr)\\n\\nprint(f'SUMMARY ok={len(oks)} err={len(errs)} remaining={len(errs)}')\\nif errs:\\n    sys.exit(2)\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9HTGbK91PNyXsnzg97lHyCBx|fc_07c2f36e4998d16e0169c7e3688fc4819b949fdda749a3550c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 scripts/active_task_cli.py advance --path checklists/ACTIVE_TASK.md --status active --updated '2026-03-28 22:16' --append-evidence '第一次逐文件下载已落地 43 个文件 / 139MB；现切换为断点续传 + 低并发重试'